<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5 Drowned, 25 Injured in Trawler Capsizing in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Five people, including women and
children, were drowned and 35 others suffered wounds Wednesday
when a trawler capsized in river Boulai in Sunamganj district,
some 350 kilometers northeast to Dhaka, the United News of
Bangladesh reported.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the mishap occurred at about 11 a.m. when the
roof of the overloaded trawler collapsed.
</P>
<P>
Locals said the death toll might go up to 15, as 10 more bodies
still remained under water.
</P>
<P>
Divers with the help of local people are carrying on the rescue
operation.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, two people were killed and 20
others injured Wednesday in a road accident on Dhaka-Chittagong
highway in Comilla, some 100 kilometers southeast of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said a bus bumped against a roadside petrol pump when
its driver lost control of steering at about 11 a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
