<HEADLINE> China Questions Election Fairness in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China Thursday voiced its
concerns over whether a free and fair election can be held in
Kosovo, as the relevant U.N. resolution is not fully implemented
in the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xu, member of the Chinese Mission to the United Nations,
told an open Security Council meeting that the security situation
on the ground remains very grave because of the terrorist actions
by Albanian extremists and the ineffective protections given by
the international peacekeeping force (KFOR).
</P>
<P>
"Our worries are whether elections can be held in a free, fair
and peaceful environment," he said, adding that the insecure
situation on the ground demonstrated that the Security Council
resolution 1244 is not fully implemented in Kosovo and the U.N.
Interim Administrative Mission in Kosovo (UNMIK) and KFOR should
work much harder to reverse the trend.
</P>
<P>
Serb refugees have a lot of difficulties in returning home in
Kosovo, and those who have returned home are very few, he said,
this is simply because the Albanian extremists are taking
terrorist actions to prevent Serb refugees from returning while
crimes against those who have returned, such as abductions and
murders, frequently took place in Kosovo. 
</P>
