<HEADLINE> Peru Affected by 4.9 Degree Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Peru's Arequipa and Moquegua cities
were shaken Thursday by a 4.9 Richter degree earthquake, without
causing victims or damages, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
According to Geophysical Institute of Peru (IGP), the quake
occurred at 00:20 o'clock local time, lasted over 30 seconds, and
had an epicenter along coasts facing the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
The earth movement affected telephone communication systems in
certain areas, and caused blocking on the South Panamerican
highway, between Arequipa and Tacna, near the border with Chile.
</P>
<P>
For fear of landslides and further quakes, some families left
their dwellings and spent the night outside their homes.
</P>
<P>
On 19 May, a four degree Richter scale quake was registered at
Chimbote city and village localities. It was situated 414
kilometers north of Peru's capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
