economic sanctions imposed on Iraq since its 1990 invasion of
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The program allows Iraq to sell limited amount of crude oil
every six months to buy food, medicine and other humanitarian
supplies to help offset the crippling impacts of the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Algeria, as an Arab country, has been calling on the U.N. as
well as the Arab League for lifting the decade-old U.N. sanctions.
