<HEADLINE> ADB to Provide Credit Assistance to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
agreed on Thursday to provide a credit assistance of about 50
million U.S. dollars to Nepal for its rural electrification
distribution and transmission project, said a press release by the
Nepali Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
After the completion of the project in 2004, 18 percent of the
total population in Nepal will have access to electricity, an
increase of 3 percent from the present level of 15 percent, the
release said.
</P>
<P>
The project, estimated to cost 94.5 million U.S. dollars, will
also be funded by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries and the Nepali government.
</P>
<P>
