<HEADLINE> France's National Day Military Parade to Be Under European Flags </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
France, which is serving as the rotating president of European
Union (EU), wishes to show its determination to push forward the
European defense construction by inviting other EU states to join
this year's parade on the Champs-Elysees, said French officials.
</P>
<P>
The parade will be headed by the Eurocorps, the Eurofor which
is the European ground force, and the European Air Group which has
seven member countries.
</P>
<P>
Britain, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Belgium and Spain,
which with France make up the European Air Group, will each send
four combat aircraft to fly across Paris while Luxembourg and
Portugal will send ground troops.
</P>
<P>
France first planned to invite all the 15 EU countries to the
parade, but it gave up the idea because of its tense relations
with Austria.
</P>
<P>
During its EU rotating presidency, France wishes to arrange an
agreement of 15 EU states on establishing a 60,000-man European
Rapid Reaction Force by 2003, said French Defense Minister Alain
Richard on Thursday. 
