<HEADLINE> European Investment Bank to Invest in Romanian Transport System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The European Investment Bank (
EIB) will grant to Romania five new loans for road, railway and
port projects, Romania's daily newspaper Curentul reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Romanian Minister of Transport Anca Boagiu as saying
the projects up for EIB assistance were assessed a week ago by EIB
experts, and the financial agreements on them will be signed in
September. Fund beneficiaries, according to international
procedures, will contribute up to half of the project value.
</P>
<P>
The current program will start in 2001 and end in 2004. A
fourth and last stage of a road rehabilitation project will also
be unfolded on 250 million euros provided by the EIB, a non-
returnable EU fund of 120 million euros, as well as on a
contribution of 130 million euros by the Romanian Government.
</P>
<P>
The EIB will also extend the Romanian Metrorex underground
transport utility a loan worth 240 million euros for extension and
upgrading.
</P>
<P>
Among the projects approved for EBI assistance are those on the
creation of a computerized train ticket issuing system, the
rehabilitation of road and railway infrastructures damaged by
floods, the installation of a water-clearing system in the port of
Constanta and a high-voltage power station in the Constanta free
trade zone. 
