<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Today (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua)-- The following are the highlights of
diplomatic news released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets U.S. Defense Secretary
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said that a healthy and stable
growth of Sino-U.S. relations not only accords with the
fundamental interests of the people of the two countries, but also
is conducive to the peace in the Asia-Pacific and the world at
large.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also chairman of the Central Military Commission,
made the remarks today while meeting with visiting U.S. Defense
Secretary William Cohen.
</P>
<P>
 Senior CPC Official Meets Niger Delegation
</P>
<P>
The development of China-Niger relations proves that the
promotion of friendship and cooperation between the two countries
conforms to the fundamental interests of the two peoples, said a
senior official of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, made the remark in a meeting
with Sekou Hamidou, president of Niger's National Movement for the
Society of Development (MNSD-NASSARA), and his delegation.
</P>
<P>
FM Spokesman on South China Sea Issue
</P>
<P>
The key to the South China Sea disputes is to avoid
complicating the issue, otherwise it will be harmful to regional
stability, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told a press conference that China has always insisted on
finding solutions to disputes with countries concerned through
friendly bilateral consultations and peaceful means, and progress
has been made in such consultations.
</P>
