<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Libyan Secretary for Foreign Affairs
Abdel Rahman Shalgam said Thursday that his country supports the
South Korean sunshine policy toward Pyongyang and evaluates the
inter-Korean summit as a historic event.
</P>
<P>
Shalgam made such comments when he was received by South Korean
president Kim Dae-jung.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Kim praised Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi
for his contribution to peace and stability in the African region.
</P>
<P>
