Libya have been well maintained since the two countries
established diplomatic ties in 1980.
</P>
<P>
South Korean participation in Libya's Great Man-Made Waterway
project is a sign of the bilateral friendly relations, Kim said,
expecting the African country to help South Korean companies take
part in more development projects.
</P>
<P>
Shalgam also held talks with his South Korean counterpart Lee
Joung-binn Thursday. The two officials discussed the political
situation on the Korean peninsula after the Pyongyang inter-Korean
summit and ways to enhance bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Libyan official briefed Lee on the outcome of his four-day
visit to Pyongyang, saying Pyongyang has the will to improve inter-
Korean ties.
</P>
<P>
Shalgam arrived here Tuesday through the direct inter-Korean
air route from Pyongyang, the first foreigner to do so. 
</P>
