<HEADLINE> Chirac Signs Clemency Decree for Prisoners on National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
signed on Thursday a presidential decree of clemency for prisoners
excluding those who have committed crimes on people under 15,
terrorism and drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The decree will alleviate the prison sentence by seven days
each month for prisoners for a maximum of four months and by two
months for all those who are condemned with suspension of prison
terms.
</P>
<P>
"Excluded from the measure are those who have committed crimes
on people less than 15 years old, and those condemned for
terrorism, drug trafficking, crimes against humanity, violence
against agents of prison administration or public force," said the
decree which was published on the eve of the national day of
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
