<HEADLINE> Romanian Leading Soccer Teams Ready for New Domestic Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Romanian leading soccer teams
are currently preparing for a new edition of Division A
championships to start on August 5, with improved game formula on
their minds.
</P>
<P>
The champion team Dinamo of Bucharest played some trial matches
in France where it beat St Etienne 3-0, defeated the Swiss team
of Lausanne 2-0, and lost 1-2 to Bastia. The team's coach Cornel
Dinu tried on this occasion new field deployment formulas,
alternatively using 4-3-3 and 4-5-1 formulas. The team was
strengthened by the acquisition of goalkeeper Florin Tene.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 champion and 2000 runners-up Rapid Bucharest, is
toning up in Belgium trained by a new coach, Anghel Iordanescu,
the coach who led Romania's national team to the 1994 and 1998
world cup finals. The club will be increased by valuable
footballers. The new Rapid captain for this year's season is
likely to be Daniel Iftodi, a technical and experienced player of
Dinamo Bucharest.
</P>
<P>
Steaua of Bucharest, the most famous Romanian club, drew FC
Malines of Belgium 1-1 in a friendly. Steaua is training in the
Netherlands. The coach, Victor Piturca, hopes to gain over Doru
Mitrita, lately playing for the Dutch club of Heereven.
</P>
<P>
Univeritatea of Craiova played a training match against the
Belgian team of La Gantoise, which it lost 1-3 after leading 1-0
up to the 84th minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
