<DOCNO> XIE20000713.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Revised Product Quality Law to Check Fake, Shoddy Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese legislators have passed an
amendment to the law on product quality, aiming to upgrade the
level of China-made products.
</P>
<P>
Li Chuanqing, director of the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision, said that the revised law further defines
the responsibility for the government to improve product quality
and stresses that enterprises must accept supervision from the
quality control departments.
</P>
<P>
The amended law includes 74 articles; the original version had
51.
</P>
<P>
Under the revised law, which goes into effect on Sept. 1,
anyone selling fake or inferior products will be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
China launched a series of clampdowns on fake and shoddy
products in recent years. However, the production of poor-quality
products is still a serious problem, especially in small
enterprises, said Li.
</P>
<P>
The amendment to the product quality law is urgent, as China
will join the World Trade Organization soon and face competition
from overseas enterprises, Li said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
