<HEADLINE> U.S. Aircraft Carrier to Visit South Africa in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- One of the world's largest
and latest aircraft carriers, the USS George Washington, is to pay
a week-long goodwill visit to South Africa in September.
</P>
<P>
South African Navy spokeswoman Lisa Hendricks said the 74,000
ton Nimitz-class nuclear powered carrier will be in Cape Town
harbor from September 4 to 10.
</P>
<P>
USS George Washington, whose length is about three rugby fields,
has a crew of more than 3,000 officers and other ranks and can
carry up to 90 aircrafts.
</P>
<P>
This is the first American aircraft carrier to visit a South
African Port in almost three decades.
</P>
<P>
Last year a helicopter-carrying combat support ship, the USS
Hall, visited Cape Town during a goodwill cruise to various
African countries.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the United States Consulate in Cape Town said
details of the USS George Washington's cruise were not available
at present but further information about its overall mission would
be released at a later date. 
