<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Niger Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The development of China-Niger
relations proves that the promotion of friendship and cooperation
between the two countries conforms to the fundamental interests of
the two peoples, said a senior official of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) here today.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, made the remark in a meeting
with Sekou Hamidou, president of Niger's National Movement for the
Society of Development (MNSD-NASSARA), and his delegation.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said bilateral cooperation in various fields has been
progressing since the restoration of diplomatic relations between
the two countries in 1996 and friendship between the two peoples
has deepened, although there was a time of twists and turns in
bilateral relations after the establishment of diplomatic
relations in 1974.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that through joint efforts, China-Niger
friendship and cooperation will develop further in the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of friendly relations between the CPC and the
MNSD-NASSARA, he said increased exchanges and study of each other'
s ruling experience will be conducive to their respective national
development, and the further development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Sekou said Niger and many other African countries have had
close relations with China, because African countries and China
have similar histories and common tasks, and China stands by the
African people in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
He said China is a multi-nationality and multi-culture country,
and China's national unity left a deep impression on his
delegation.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the conviction that the Chinese people will score
even more achievements, and achieve the complete reunification of
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is visiting China at the CPC's invitation.
</P>
