<HEADLINE> China Issues Regulations on Safety Supervision of Special Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China recently issued regulations
on quality and safety supervision for special products and
equipment, including elevators and recreational devices.
</P>
<P>
The regulation, issued by the State Quality and Technical
Supervision Bureau, stipulates that the design and production of
special facilities must meet national related quality standards
and safety requirements.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturers without production and safety licenses are
forbidden to produce the special equipment, according to the
regulation, which will be implemented on Oct. 1.
</P>
<P>
In addition to requirements for designers and producers of
special equipment, the regulation also asks the users be
responsible for the proper usage and maintenance of the devices.
</P>
<P>
China currently has over one million items in the special
products category, including elevators, recreational devices,
cableways and boilers. A number of accidents caused by safety
problems of these devices have resulted in deaths and economic
losses in China recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
