<HEADLINE> Israeli Police Arrest Six Palestinians in East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 13 (XInhua) -- Israeli police arrested six
Palestinians after an exchange of fire in east Jerusalem on
Thursday, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The policemen, who were undercover on a mission in the Ras al-
Amud neighborhood near the Old City in east Jerusalem, were
attacked Thursday morning by a group of armed men from a house.
There was an exchange of fire and more police were called in.
</P>
<P>
Police reinforcements surrounded the building and the six men
gave themselves in.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a police source as saying the armed men were
criminals and not terrorists. They were believed to have hidden
themselves in the Ras al-Amud house following a criminal offense in
northern Jerusalem on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nobody was injured in the exchange of fire, said the report.
