<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Seizes Over One Million Pirated Articles in Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore authorities seized
more than one million pirated articles and apprehended over 800
persons in their anti-piracy actions in the first half of this
year, officials from Singapore's Trade Development Board (TDB) and
the police told a press conference Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They said the enforcement units conducted a total of 1,147
raids on shopping centers, storage locations and makeshift stalls
and recovered infringing products with market value of some eight
million Singapore dollars (about 4.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the same period last year, 1,228 raids were conducted and a
total of 680,858 infringing articles were seized.
</P>
<P>
The officials attributed the results to the intensified anti-
piracy efforts, noting the police have upgraded the Intellectual
Property Rights (IPR) Warrant Unit to a branch level and the newly
established Intellectual Property Rights Branch (IPRB) has also
been moved from the Commercial Crime Division to the Specialized
Crime Division of the Criminal Investigation Department.
</P>
<P>
They also said Singapore will be beefing up intellectual
property education campaign this year to help people understand
and accept the need for IPR protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000713.0111 </DOCNO>
