<HEADLINE> Manila to Pursue Peace Despite MILF's Call for Holy War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Thursday that it is ready to pursue just and lasting peace in
Mindanao despite the call of the leadership of the Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) for a holy war against the government.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said in a radio speech that
this goal remains President Joseph Estrada's top priority for
Mindanao, which his administration is determined to transform into
the country's food basket.
</P>
<P>
"We are still determined to pursue peace and we will do that
with or without the MILF," Zamora said.
</P>
<P>
He also described as a big mistake the decision of the MILF
leadership to call for a jihad (holy war), stressing anew that the
government is not at war with the Bangsamoro people.
</P>
<P>
Zamora said the government will not force the MILF to accept
peace, but is ready to respond to any abuse that the group may
commit against the people.
</P>
<P>
"If they want war, how will we respond to that? We cannot force
them to accept peace if they don't want it," he said.
</P>
<P>
President Estrada, Zamora said, is set to convene the Mindanao
Coordinating Council (MCC) to discuss the problem in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting would include the drafting of a proposed
measure to be submitted to Congress seeking extra powers for the
president to speed up the implementation of development projects
in the south.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the president described the declaration of a holy
war by MILF Chairman Hashim Salamat as unwarranted, saying that
the government has not declared war against the Bangsamoro people.
</P>
<P>
The President said that as Commander in Chief of the Armed
Forces of the Philippines (AFP), he had only ordered government
troops to step up efforts in running after MILF rebels "who have
violated the ceasefire agreement who committed other criminal or
illegal acts."
</P>
<P>
The president was reacting to the reported call by Salamat for
his people to rise in jihad or armed struggle against the
government, after the fall of Camp Abubakar, the MILF's main
headquarters, to government hands early this week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
