<HEADLINE> China Cutting Down Coal Production, Stockpile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China has made headway in the
efforts to reduce coal production and stockpiles for balanced
supply and demand and keep this year's coal output within 900
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xianzheng, deputy director of the State Administration of
Coal Industry, said here today that so far the number of legal
coal production enterprises has been cut down from 300,000 to 80,
000 nationwide, with a large number of illegal small coal mines
closed down.
</P>
<P>
The situation of coal supply exceeding demand has also been
eased to some degree, he added.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the country's large state-owned coal
enterprises will take further steps in the latter half of this
year to produce according to market demand, adjust their product
mix, and lower production costs in a bid to turn losses into
profits. 
</P>
