<HEADLINE> China Sets Plan for Development of New and Renewable Energy Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The State Economic and Trade
Commission (SETC) has worked out a plan on the development of new
and renewable energy resources in the next 15 years, according to
an SETC official.
</P>
<P>
Bai Rongchun, director in charge of the resources utilization
under the SETC, said by 2015 China will annually develop new and
renewable energy resources amounting to 43 million tons of coal
equivalent (TCE), accounting for two percent of the country's
total energy consumption.
</P>
<P>
With the new and renewable energy resources, the country's coal
consumption will be cut by 60 million tons, which will amount to
reduction of pollutants including 30 million tons of carbon
dioxide and 2.1 million tons of sulfur dioxide, nitrogen oxides
and soot.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the volume of China's annual exploitation and
utilization of new and renewable energy resources amount to three
million TCE, accounting for about 0.2 percent of the total
commercial energy consumption.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the largest energy producers and consumers,
especially the world's largest coal consumer, said Bai at a press
conference held here today. He noted that heavy reliance on coal
has had severe environmental impacts.
</P>
<P>
Bai noted that China has made great efforts in the past years
to readjust its energy utilization structure and decided to take
effective measures to solve the energy problem.
</P>
<P>
According to the new plan, by the year 2015, the annual output
of new energy development and of related equipment manufacturing
will reach nearly 67 billion yuan. The industry as a whole will
provide nearly 0.5 million job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
To promote the development of new energy resources, the SETC
and five other departments will jointly sponsor the International
Environment, Renewable Energy and Energy Efficiency Exhibition and
Conference, to be held on November 28-December 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
