<DOCNO> XIE20000713.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Up at Thursday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
firmed 1.19 points or 1.07 percent to the intraday high of 112.17
points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 54.72 million HK dollars, 24.94 million more
than Wednesday's total.
</P>
<P>
As has been the case recently, narrow-range trading had a grip
on the market in early trading before positive numbers helped to
push the index noticeably higher, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
China's exports rose a hefty 38.3 percent in the first half of
2000 to hit 114.5 billion U.S. dollars, according to sources from
the General Customs. Imports increased as well, hitting 102.1
billion. The trade surplus stood at 12 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports of garments, steel and electrical products showed the
biggest growth, with shares getting an extra boost today.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers by 34 to 11, with another 8
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Orient Elect rose 6.53 percent to 4.08 HK dollars while Nanjing
P&AMP;T added 6.01 percent to 3.00 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Huafa Elect shed 2.07 percent to 1.89 HK dollars while Yantai
Changyu dipped 1.70 percent to close at 3.47 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The market is steadily gaining strength amid investors'
optimism for further signs of an improving economy, Homeway said.
</P>
</TEXT>
