<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Doomed to Failure in Entering UN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan is doomed to failure in its
effort to enter the United Nations whatever tricks it will play,
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said today.
</P>
<P>
As a province of China, Taiwan has no qualification to enter
this international organization, Zhu stressed at a regular press
conference this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated that the United Nations, an inter-
governmental international organization, consists only of
sovereign states.
</P>
<P>
"The government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate one representing China, and Taiwan cannot enter the U.N.
and all of its agencies under any names and through any methods."
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, the General Committee of each U.N. General Assembly
has refused to include the so-called representation of Taiwan in
its agenda, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
