<HEADLINE> Philippine Peso Remains Firm on Technical Correction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine peso stayed firmer
against the greenback Thursday as the peso extended its technical
correction.
</P>
<P>
The peso averaged 44.509, stronger compared to Wednesday's
close of 44.665.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said banks which bought dollars before are starting to
unload their positions.
</P>
<P>
"Technical charts show at 45 pesos, the dollar was overbought.
So banks have been selling their dollars," a dealer at a foreign
bank said.
</P>
<P>
They also said the peso recovered due to the absence of oil
companies that bought dollars for import requirements.
</P>
<P>
Value of trade turnover reached 95.5 million dollars in early
trade Thursday. 
</P>
