<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 830,000 Ugandans Killed by AIDS in Two Decades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- An estimated 838,000 Ugandans had
died of AIDS by the end of 1999, while in 1999 alone the death
toll reached 110,000, according to Minister of Health Crispus
Kiyonga.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1.44 million people in Uganda were living with HIV/
AIDS at the end of 1999, among them about 1,294,200 were adults,
the minister said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
At the 13th international AIDS conference in Durban, Uganda was
one of the three countries hailed for successfully combating AIDS,
said a New Vision report on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The number of people infected with HIV/AIDS in the country has
dropped sharply from over 30 percent of the total population in
the 1980s and early 1990s to the current 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Awareness of HIV/AIDS remains high in the east Africa country,
and about 80 million condoms will be required for use this year,
according to the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
