<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Closes At New Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index
closed at 1979.20 points on Thursday, up 5.83 points or 0.30
percent compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume stood at 19.35 billion yuan (2.33
billion U.S. dollars), 29.8 percent more than the previous session
's 14.91 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is the third consecutive day when the market index
finished at a new record closing-up high. Investors' confidence in
the iron and steel counters pushed the index as high as 1,984.07
points in the morning, the highest ever in history.
</P>
<P>
However, many investors sold iron and steel stocks afterwards
and shifted their interest in the Internet-related and other hi-
tech firms. As a result, the market index plunged, then slowly
climbed up and fluctuated all day, according to Beijing-based on-
line financial and securities advisory company Homeway.
</P>
<P>
The Custom's mid-year reports about exports helped buoy the
market as investors became more confident about China's economic
growth this year, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's exports rose 38.3 percent in the
first half of 2000 to reach 114.5 billion U.S. dollars. Imports
increased by 36.2 percent to hit 102.1 billion U.S. dollars as
well, leading to a trade surplus of 12.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.518 billion shares changed hands today, and market
gainers outnumbered losers by 260 to 226, with the prices of
another 8 stocks remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Xingchen New Chemical Material Co. Ltd surged 10.01 percent to
18.69 yuan per share while Shanghai Belling Co. Ltd, Grinm
Semiconductor Materials Co. Ltd and Shenyang Neu-Alpine Software
Co. Ltd all grew by 10 percent to close at 26.73 yuan, 35.86 yuan
and 36.85 yuan respectively.
</P>
<P>
Beiman Special Steel Co. Ltd was the biggest loser, with its
price shedding 7.56 percent to 7.58 yuan per share on profit-
taking.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high tomorrow, Homeway said.
</P>
</TEXT>
