</P>
<P>
The sub-index advanced 34.12 points or 0.71 percent to close
the day at 4,839.13 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 18.82 billion yuan, 52.3 percent more than
Wednesday's 12.36 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index opened high today. It fluctuated
all day and finally closed at a new record high. Investors'
interest turned from the iron and steel sector to Internet-
related and other high-technology stocks, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Customs' half year report about the surge of Chinese
exports helped the market rally as investors were more confident
about China's economic growth this year. The report said that
China's exports rose 38.3 percent in the first half of 2000 from a
year earlier to 114.5 billion US dollars, and the imports
increased 36.2 percent to 102.1 billion US dollars, leading to a
first-half surplus of about 12 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The market losers beat gainers by 277 to 201, with the price of
one stock unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The price increases of Chengzhi Shareholding Co. Ltd and
Langchao Electronics Information Industry Co. Ltd hit the ten
percent daily limit. The former rose 10.01 percent to 31.22 yuan
per share, and the latter, ten percent, to 30.48 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Sun-Wind Chemical Industry Group Co., Ltd was the
biggest loser. Its price dropped 7.92 percent to close at 9.07
yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Analysts note that the market is likely to fluctuate within a
narrow range and try a new high tomorrow.  
</P>
