<HEADLINE> China's T-bond Market Inactive on Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond extended the narrow
fluctuations on Thursday with thin trading. The trading volume
totaled 1.36 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that 010004 finally climbed up 0.11 percent to
close at 120.11, a record high since the bond made its debut in
early June. Profit taking on the bond may set in during the
following trading days.
</P>
<P>
All the other bonds fluctuated within a narrow range of less
than 0.10 percent. Three of the total six current treasuries lost,
two gained and the other one remained unchanged, said Beijing-
based financial advisory company Homeway.
</P>
<P>
The stock indices on the two bourses closed up at new record
highs today. However, four companies announced their interim
losses and more companies turned to be loss makers after new share
sales or share placements, a negative sentiment that may dampen
the stock and T-bond market.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market was comparatively active. The trade volume
on three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day repo transactions
increased by 5.99 billion yuan to 7.5 billion yuan. However, the
interest rate on the three-day product tumbled 0.22 percentage
points to 3.80 percent.  
</P>
