<HEADLINE> IASIA Annual Conference Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The annual conference of the
International Association of Schools and Institutes of
Administration (IASIA) closed here today.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 Chinese and overseas delegates participated in the
four-day conference.
</P>
<P>
It is decided that the next annual conference will be held in
Athens, Greece, between July 7 and 13, 2001.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the participants read their papers and
discussed issues concerning the conference's theme of "Improving
Accountability, Efficiency and Responsiveness in Government: Ideas
and Lessons for the New Millennium".
</P>
<P>
They held the same opinion that China has achieved remarkable
achievements in administration restructuring, speaking highly of
the Chinese government's effort in remolding its image by fighting
corruption and adopting an open administrating and participatory
democracy.
</P>
<P>
IASIA was founded in 1962 as a branch of IIAS and became an
independent organization in 1971. The IASIA is headquartered in
Brussels, with 170 members from over 70 nations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
