<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motherland Party Leader to Join Turkish Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Mesut Yilmaz, leader of the ruling
partner Motherland Party (ANAP), will be appointed state minister
for European Union Affairs after the parliament recently cleared
him of corruption allegations.
</P>
<P>
In a 40-minute talks with Yilmaz Wednesday, Prime Minister
Bulent Ecevit invited him to take up the vacant seat in his three-
way coalition government, Anatolia News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz accepted the offer. It was expected that the decision
will be presented to President Ahmet Necdet Sezer for approval on
Thursday, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Last year when Ecevit, leader of the Democratic Left Party
(DSP), formed the current coalition together with Deputy Prime
Minister Develet Bahceli's Nationalist Action Party (MHP) and
Yilmaz's ANAP, the ANAP leader rejected a role in the cabinet as he
was facing eight corruption charges.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz, who had served as prime minister three times, was
accused of abusing power for self-interests during his tenure.
</P>
<P>
Last month, tension was brewing in Ankara once again as three
MHP deputies joined the opposition deputies in a parliamentary
investigation commission in a bid to file Yilmaz to the Supreme
Court over allegations of graft.
</P>
<P>
The move soured relations between ANAP and MHP, the two ruling
partners, and jeopardized the coalition's stability which Ecevit
has strived for and was imperative for his economic reforms
program.
</P>
<P>
Rumors emerged that MHP and ANAP are trying to damage each other
as a part of their election strategy as both parties are aiming to
woo nationalist and conservative votes, in the absence of the pro-
Islamic opposition Virtue Party (FP).
</P>
<P>
The possibility of an early election is real because Turkish
Constitutional Court will decide whether FP is the successor to the
defunct Islamic Welfare Party or not in October.
</P>
<P>
If the court makes a "yes" verdict, the FP will be closed and 70
of the 103 FP deputies in the 550-member parliament will be
dismissed.
</P>
<P>
Under Turkey's Constitution, if five percent, or about 28 of the
parliament's deputies are absent, an early parliamentary election
should be held within three months.
</P>
<P>
After the decision to send Yilmaz to the Supreme Court for trial
on graft charges failed in the parliament, the coalition left
behind the tension, if tentatively.
</P>
<P>
Also, the vote in the parliament meant to have cleared Yilmaz of
the corruption allegations, paving the way for his entry into the
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
"Mesut Yilmaz is an experienced statesman with time in the
government. This is a great advantage, ensuring coordination among
public and private institutions," said Ecevit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000713.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
