<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Average Per Capita Income Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's monthly average per capita
income was 295,000 Vietnamese dong (VND) (21.07 U.S. dollars) in
1999, an increase of 30 percent on the 1996 figure, Vietnam's
official news agency VNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The monthly average per capita income was 832,500 VND (59.46
dollars) in urban areas and 225,000 VND (16.07 dollars) in rural
areas, increases of 63.4 percent and 19.7 percent, respectively,
VNA quoted the General Statistics Office of the country as saying.
</P>
<P>
The poverty rate in the country was reduced to 13.33 percent
from 17.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
With increasing incomes, households invested more money in
building houses and purchasing other fixed assets. 
</P>
