<HEADLINE> Thorpe Says He Is Clean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Australian swimming teenage
sensation Thorpe said he would release the results of his next
drugs test to prove he is clean.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old world champion said he had asked the Australian
Sports Drug Agency to release his sample results.
</P>
<P>
Doping suspicions over Thorpe resurfaced after allegations by a
German swimmer, reported in a Sydney newspaper, that Thorpe's size
17 feet were the result of using human growth hormone.
</P>
<P>
"Any suggestion that the size of Ian's feet are associated with
human growth hormone are absolutely ridiculous," his mother
Margaret Thorpe said.
</P>
<P>
"From a very, very young age, I couldn't find booties to fit
him. Big feet run in the family."
</P>
<P>
Thorpe's manager Dave Flaskas described the allegations "
ludicrous".
</P>
<P>
"He's totally discarded the accusation," Flaskas said. "He's at
training this morning, the whole thing's quite ludicrous. He might
have big feet, but the Germans have the big mouths."
</P>
<P>
"Every time they accuse him he goes quicker. The last time they
did that he broke a world record by one and a half seconds," he
added. 
</P>
