<HEADLINE> China Scores Historic High in Import and Export Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- For the first time in history,
China registered over 100 billion U.S. dollars in both import and
export volumes in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
China's import and export volume reached 216.6 billion U.S.
dollars from January to June, up 37.3 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The export volume rose 38.3 percent to hit 114.5 billion U.S.
dollars, while the import volume rose 36.2 percent to hit 102.1
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In June alone, the total volume of import and export reached 42.
5 billion U.S. dollars, 42.5 percent over the same month of last
year. The import volume in June reached 20.3 billion U.S. dollars
while the export volume was 22.2 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
