<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
Thursday expressed satisfaction with his three-day visit to
Germany, hopeful that good Tehran-Berlin ties will have a favorable
impact on Iran's ties with the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters upon his return from Germany, Khatami said
his talks with German President Johnannes Rau and Chancellor
Gerhard Schroeder as well as other senior German officials have
been positive and good.
</P>
<P>
He added Tehran and Berlin are determined to expand relations in
all spheres, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Germany, he said, is interested in playing a greater role in the
world political scene, which is befitting for Germany's economic,
technical and scientific status. Relations with Iran, which enjoys
an excellent geopolitical position, are important for the country,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
The president pointed out, however, that the satisfactory visit
does not mean there is no difference between Iran and Germany. He
said only through talks can these misunderstandings be partly
removed.
</P>
<P>
Khatami expressed hope that his visit will serve as a prelude to
good and decisive ties between Iran and Germany and will be
beneficial for peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The German visit was the first by an Iranian president since the
1979 Islamic revolution. 
