<DOCNO> XIE20000713.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Selects Bangkok as Regional Program Management Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has chosen
Bangkok as the site of its Program Management Office (PMO) for
Asia, which will be in charge of promoting information technology
(IT) and communications between Europe and Asia, the Thai News
Agency (TNA) reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The office, to be established over the next five years with the
total budget of 19 million ECU, will coordinate with the PMO
headquarters in Brussels, in cooperative projects, aimed to
develop IT and communication links between the two regions, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok-PMO office would also support transfers of know-how
and technology from advanced companies in Europe to their business
partners in Asia, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Brussels-based PMO is currently linked with the EU's 15
member states, and 17 other countries in Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
