<HEADLINE> Injury Forces Thomas out of European Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- European and Commonwealth 400
meters champion Iwan Thomas has pulled out of the British team for
this weekend's European Cup team event in Gateshead, England.
</P>
<P>
Thomas, who had been due to run in the 4x400m relay, is
suffering a hamstring problem.
</P>
<P>
"It's only a niggle and I really don't want to talk about it,"
Thomas was quoted as saying in Thursday's edition of the The
Guardian newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Thomas joins javelin thrower Steve Backley, triple jumper
Jonathan Edwards and 110m hurdler Colin Jackson, who have already
withdrawn from the event. 
