<HEADLINE> China Makes Progress in Hepatitis C Vaccine Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese researchers have designed
a compound vaccine after four years of tests on mice, rabbits and
monkeys, and found it is resistant to Hepatitis C.
</P>
<P>
A thesis on the research was recently published in the country'
s leading scientific journal -- Chinese Science Bulletin.
</P>
<P>
The researchers, from Fudan University, No.1 Medical College of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army, and a medical college in
southwest China's Yunnan Province, have used gene engineering
techniques in the development of the vaccine.
</P>
<P>
Hepatitis has prevailed for a long time and spread widely in
the world, especially in developing countries in Asia, Africa and
Latin America.
</P>
<P>
But researchers said they still have a long way to go before
the vaccine is applied to human beings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
