<HEADLINE> China's IT Industry Continues to Grow Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China's telecommunications
operation and service sectors saw a robust 27.1 percent growth of
revenue in the first five months of this year, official figures
show.
</P>
<P>
According to Cheng Guanghui, spokesman of the Ministry of
Information Industry (MII), telecom operation and service sectors
reaped in 123.47 billion yuan of revenue during January to May.
</P>
<P>
Cheng told a press conference this morning that sales turnover
of the manufacturing sector of IT products soared 32.7 percent to
200.7 billion yuan in the five-month period.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, exports of IT products jumped by 43.5 percent on
yearly basis to 59.94 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the five-month period, China turned out 2.08 million
personal computers, more than doubling the figure for the same
period of last year, Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
During the period, China also produced 18.86 million cellular
phones, 143.3 percent more than the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
