Latuconsina complained about the lack of authority he holds in
restoring order.
</P>
<P>
"Although I'm the civil emergency ruler, I cannot give orders
but only ask for immediate security measures," Latuconsina, who is
Maluku governor, was quoted by the Jakarta Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Violence has been rife in the Maluku capital of Ambon since the
enactment of the civil emergency in the province. One of the worst
incidences was the predawn attack which totally destroyed the 30-
hectare compound of the state Pattimura University and three
neighboring villages on July 4.
</P>
<P>
As of Wednesday night, gunfire and explosions were still heard
coming from some areas in Ambon. School and business activities
remained on a standstill. People were seen queuing at the banks
for cash. 
</P>
