<HEADLINE> Russia Hopes Romania to Remain Neutral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Romania, as a sovereign state,
should remain neutral, said visiting Chairman of the State Duma of
Russia Gennady Seleznev at a press conference here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It is unnecessary for Romania to join an alliance, because it
does not face any threat, the Romanian Press quoted Seleznev, the
Russian parliament speaker, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia strongly opposes any move to expand the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO), said Seleznev, emphasizing that NATO,
as a military bloc, should have been disbanded as the Warsaw
Treaty Organization did in July 1991.
</P>
<P>
Romania has its own right to decide whether to join NATO or not.
But Russia "will certainly feel unhappy" when it is surrounded by
NATO troops, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The NATO bombing of Yugoslav in 1999 sets "a bad example" and
such bombing can solve no issues, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the pollution caused by the bombing, Seleznev said,
NATO alone should take the responsibility for the environmental
pollution and detriments to the health of the local people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
