<HEADLINE> Largest Women-Trafficking Gang Unearthed in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Polish police Wednesday detained
more than 10 racketeers of a cross-border gang involved in
kidnapping and forcing women into the sex trade in Grojec, a town
dozens of miles away from Warsaw, according to a TV report.
</P>
<P>
Uncovering the largest women-trafficking gang in years in the
country, police rescued about a dozen women and underage girls.
</P>
<P>
The gang, made up mainly of Poles and Bulgarians, had been
trafficking in women and young girls from Belarus, Bulgaria,
Romania, Ukraine and Poland and forced them into sex slavery.
</P>
<P>
Some of the women and girls were locked up in Grojec, losing
their freedom and suffering from maltreatment. A women who made
attempts to escape was beaten up and had her legs broken, said the
TV report. 
</P>
