<HEADLINE> China Builds More Key Labs at Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China has made remarkable progress
in construction of university key labs. Nearly two thirds of the
150 state-level key labs are located in universities, said an
official of the Ministry of Education (MOE).
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yaoxue, director of the Science and Technology Department
of MOE, said that during the 1994-1998 period, 71.5 percent of
projects supported by the national natural science foundation came
to university key labs.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out that university key labs are important bases
for expanding high-level basic research and nurturing experts, as
well as centers for academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that MOE has taken a series of measures to improve
university key labs, which include fund increase for key labs and
visiting scholars.
</P>
<P>
The number of university key labs sponsored by MOE will
increase from 44 to 125, and MOE will give priority to fields like
life science, bio-technology, information technology, and new
materials.
</P>
<P>
MOE plans to arrange 100 million yuan as special fund for
visiting scholars in key labs this year. MOE sponsored 604
visiting scholars in 133 key labs in 49 universities in 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
