<HEADLINE> Beijing to Become China's Major Software Hub </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital Beijing is
determined to become the country's top software development and
production base in three years, vice-mayor Lin Wenyi has said.
</P>
<P>
In its recently finished plan for the Zhongguancun Science Park
in the northwest, the city has included the design for a software
park in the Haidian District.
</P>
<P>
The vice-mayor said Beijing has strong advantages in
technologies and talents that are essential for the development of
the software industry.
</P>
<P>
In fact, Beijing's income from software products and services
already accounts for one-third of the national total, Lin said.
</P>
<P>
To promote the development of the software industry, the city
authority cut the value-added tax rate for the sector from 17
percent to six percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Lin said Beijing will co-operate with foreign companies in
setting up a software designers' training center and a special
fund for the support of medium and small-sized software
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the city has already formed an information
technology promotion center and will draft still more policies to
support the development of the software industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
