<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Host Asian Women Junior Handball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The sixth Asian Women Junior
Handball Championship, a qualifying meet of the World Junior
Handball Tournament, will be held in Dhaka on July 25, Commerce
Minister Abdul Jalil, Chairman of the organizing committee told a
news conference here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seven countries and regions will be pool into two groups for
the preliminary rounds competition from July 25 to 27. The top two
group finishers will enter in the semi-finals on July 29.
</P>
<P>
The Group A comprises title holders South Korea, Chinese Taipei,
India and Nepal. Hosts Bangladesh, which is take part in major
Asian meet for the first time, has been placed in the tough Group
B along with China and championship favorites Japan.
</P>
<P>
Three top teams from ensuing seven-team Dhaka meet will qualify
for the World Junior Handball Championship to be held in Hungary
from July 29 to August 12, 2001.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Bangladesh is to play the opening match against defending
runners-up China at the Shaheed Suhrawardy National Indoor Stadium.
State-run Bangladesh Television will telecast all the 14 matches
live.
</P>
<P>
A organizing committee, headed by Commerce Minister Abdul Jalil,
and 13 subcommittees are now working round-the-clock for
successful holding of the prestigious meet to be organized by
Bangladesh Handball Federation (BHF) under the supervision of
Asian Handball Federation (AHF). 
</P>
