<HEADLINE> Putin Urges Cooperation Among Branches of Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin
has called on the country's different branches of power to stop
their tug-of-war and resume cooperation for the well-being of the
nation.
</P>
<P>
State authority is in short supply in Russia, so balance and
cooperation between the branches of authority must be urgently re-
instituted, Putin said in an interview to be published in the
Friday edition of the Izvestia newspaper, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Putin was apparently referring to the opposition in the
Federation Council to measures he proposed on the reorganization
of the upper house of parliament. The measures, already passed by
the State Duma lower house of parliament, remain stranded in the
council.
</P>
<P>
The bills on restructuring the authority "remain within the
logic of setting the rules because every state or municipal body
of authority must have clear-cut responsibilities as well as
rights," Putin said.
</P>
<P>
The branches of authority must stop playing tug-of-war and
working on their own corporate or personal ambitions rather than
the interests of the state, he said.
</P>
<P>
The president said he wants to put an end to the situation in
which Russians seem to be subjects of different regions rather
than citizens of the same country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
