<TEXT>
<P>
Rome, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Italy will donate some 61 billion
lire(about 30 million U.S. dollars) to help the fight against Aids
in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Italian Foreign Minister Rino Serri said at a press conference
Thursday that 41 billion lire will be used immediately while the
remaining 20 will be used later.
</P>
<P>
The press conference was connected by audio to Durban where the
13th International Conference on Aids was taking place.
</P>
<P>
Guidelines were discussed with Stefano Vella, director of the
program for Aids research of the Superior Health Institute and
President of the International Aids society.
</P>
<P>
In the final phase an open dialogue with African countries
interested in enacting the program will be set.
</P>
<P>
The African countries interested are about 20. They are all
from western and eastern Africa, the Horn of Africa, the Great
lakes region and the Gulf of Guinea.
</P>
<P>
Italian Senate Thursday passed the bill to cancel its third
world debt of 6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Serri said at the press conference that Italy is one of the
first countries in the world to cancel its third world debt.
</P>
