<HEADLINE> Greece Takes Measures to Combat Nationwide Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Greek government Thursday
decided to take drastic measures to combat the spate of forest
fires around the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after an emergency government meeting chaired by
Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis Thursday, Greece's Interior
Minister Vasso Papandreou said that the measures included putting
the armed forces on full alert to free up fire-fighting forces,
asking for help from abroad, hiring more fire-fighting aircraft
and the emergency hiring of seasonal staff with previous
experience in fighting forest fires.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government characterized the situation in the
country as very difficult due to the strong winds and the
scorching temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Currently, more than 100 forest fires were reported in Greece
and a blaze in western Attica Thursday fanned dense smoke over the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 11,500 hectares of forest and farm land have been
destroyed by the wildfires which were believed to be caused by
both the high temperatures and arsons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
