<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Car Prices Much More Expensive Than Europe's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The massive gap between new car
prices in Britain and those in Europe has widened, according to
figures compiled by the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
The figures reveal that the price of the Vauxhall Astra is 65
percent higher in the UK than the cheapest EU country, while the
Renault Laguna is 60 percent more, a Citroen Xentia 41 percent
more and a three-series BMW 33 percent higher.
</P>
<P>
Despite the huge gulf in prices, the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT) said the figures did not reflect
the fall in prices during the past six months.
</P>
<P>
It said that the reason for the growing gap was the 10 percent
fall in the value of the euro against the pound since November.
</P>
<P>
According to the SMMT, the value of the pound has risen by 44
percent since May 1996 and 10 percent in the six months since the
previous European price survey.
</P>
<P>
The figures come at a time when the UK motor industry is
reaching the end of a consultation period in which it has to
respond to government demands to implement a package of measures
designed to lower the price of new cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
