<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Start Final Phase of Land Redistribution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
Friday said the government will start the final phase of land
redistribution on Saturday, despite criticisms from countries like
Britain.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the burial of former Political Commissar Cephas
Cele who died in Bulawayo last week, Mugabe said the government
will not tolerate any impediments on the land issue because it had
stayed unsolved for too long.
</P>
<P>
"When we talk about the need to redistribute land, voices ring
from those who empowered themselves yesterday, they say we are
practising racism and grabbing land," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the invasion of about 1,600 mostly white-owned
commercial farms by war veterans was a clear sign that blacks were
desperate to retake their forefathers' land stolen by settlers.
</P>
<P>
He said Britain, Zimbabwe's former colonial master, had refused
to give financial assistance for the land redistribution program.
</P>
<P>
"The call still rings, give us our land. I say to you, your
land starts coming tomorrow and tomorrow is D-day for us," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean government has announced that it will
compulsorily acquire 5 million hectares of land from the white
farmers to distribute landless Zimbabweans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
