<HEADLINE> Cooperation on Education, Training to Dominate CPLP Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Community of Portuguese-
speaking Countries (CPLP) is likely to give priority in its next
mandate to cooperation on education and training among member
states, said reports reaching here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the CPLP Secretariat, officials from the seven
Portuguese-speaking countries began talks on cooperation within
the community, making preparations for the CPLP summit scheduled
for next Monday and Tuesday in the Mozambican capital Maputo.
</P>
<P>
Besides, other proposed areas for cooperation included public
administration, the establishment of regional centers and the
creation of a community database, said Felizbela Godinho, economic
advisor to the CPLP executive secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The nomination of the new CPLP executive secretary will also be
discussed by the participants of the summit.
</P>
<P>
CPLP groups Portugal, Angola, Brazil, Cape Verde, Guinea-Bissau,
Mozambique and Sao Tome and Principe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
