<HEADLINE> Nigerian Government Declares Site of Oil Pipeline Fire Disaster Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government has declared
the site of last Monday's oil pipeline fire disaster area and
barred further entry into it, press here reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken to avert further explosion because the
air was still pregnant with petrol fumes, according to Environment
Minister of State Ime Okopido,
</P>
<P>
The minister, who led a Federal Government team to the scene on
Thursday, directed security agencies in the state, the Pipelines
and Products Marketing Company (PPMC) and the local government to
provide an indefinite round-the-clock security in the area, adding
that defaulters of the order should be apprehended.
</P>
<P>
The explosion happened last Monday when people were using
buckets to collect petrol flowing from the pipeline after it had
been punctured by thieves on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
About 300 people have been confirmed dead in the accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
