<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish-Argentine Oil Co. Issues 1.25 Bln Dls Global Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Petroleum Company Repsol YPF
has issued a global 5 year bond for 1.25 billion U.S. dollars,
announced Thursday the Hispanic-Argentine company.
</P>
<P>
According to a press communique from the company, the bond has
an effective interest rate of 7.471 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bond, whose initial offer was of 700 million dollars, was
increased to 1.25 billion owing to the strong demand registered on
international markets.
</P>
<P>
This is the first global bond issued by a Spanish firm and
that has been placed at the same time on American, European and
Asian markets.  
</P>
