<HEADLINE> Andean Parliament Backs Colombian Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Andean Parliament met Thursday in
Bogota to back Colombia's peace process and examine political and
economic problems of member countries.
</P>
<P>
"We will approve a support statement of the multiple measures
Colombia's government is putting forward to reach peace", said
Peruvian congressman Andres Reggiardo Sayan, President of the
Andean Parliament, made up by representatives of Colombia,
Venezuela, Ecuador, Peru and Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
He added that the two-day meeting serves to examine "the
situation inside each parliament and of our own countries" and
present recommendations for yearly meetings of presidents of the 5
Andean nations. 
</P>
